tip.text: Apparently the 2nd lodge to be built in North Island after Huka Lodge. Very picturesque views from each room. Idyllic location to sit back and relax

Tried the shashuka and chicken schnitzel sandwich which was nice. Very well made coffees.
It is unfortunate but the best rated hotel in Auckland has one of the worst kitchens I know. Never order high tea here. None of the ordered in dishes taste good. And for $60 it is a definite rip off
Asian fusion food which seems to over do the spices instead of leaving it a little milder. Obvious problem when the chef looks middle eastern but is in charge of whipping up all the flavours.
This place is average considering its location right in the heart of ponsonby with some of the best quality restaurants around. Sashimi pieces were 3mm thick slices. Was disappointed.
Value for money ramen. About 10-15 for a bowl of ramen depending on what you pick but this place opens till 2am. Its right beside a seedy looking Japanese club.
